postcontent: Old Model three screw flattop 357 made in 1960.  Has been converted but have the parts in the sealed bag as they were returned from Ruger. Gun is in excellent condition with 2 or 3 small specks on the frame, most notably on the trigger guard visible in the photos about the size of a flea, and a hairline scratch caused by the ejector rod head under the barrel.  Grips are not original to the gun, they are pearloid and the right one has a fracture but would probably be replaced anyway with an original wood or rubber grip.  Almost inperceptable "plumming" on the loading gate which is normal in one of this era.  This one has the less common 6 groove  4 5/8" barrel. No box.  Nice old flattop and getting harder to find in this condition.  Possible trades, but not on Glocks or other plasticware.

title: For Sale:  300 Blackout brass 95$ per 500
postcontent: This, in my honest opinion, is the one of the best options of brass for blackout. This brass is 100% WCC made from once fired 5.56 with a single 2011 headstamp. It has a stronger primer pocket compared to the other brass I run and I seem to get more reloadings from it comparatively. Primer pockets are swagged, not reemed, just enough that t5he primers go in while still giving it a snug fit for long life. I trim the brass to 1.355 which is closer to the lower tolerance so your brass should last longer between trimmings. The way these are trimmed some might have a slight burr on the inside of the case. These can be removed with a deburring chamfer or running them through a resizing die. I dont think it necessarily needs removed and I dont when I reload them.
